She, however, asserted her independence, vowing not to pursue politically motivated prosecutions. Bondi's response to Democrats' inquiries on Trump's "stolen election" claim drew mixed reactions, with some critics accusing her of avoiding the issue. Republicans praised her qualifications, while Democrats remain skeptical of her ability to serve without bias. Bondi's marital status and personal life were also subjects of interest, with some supporters expressing admiration for her appearance during the hearing. The Justice Department's commitment to avoid an "enemies list" was emphasized by Bondi, emphasizing her objective to uphold the law.
